    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>POISON COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>TOO EXPENSIVE</span><b>, By Fortunnis</b> <small>(4/9/2001)</small><br><br>No merchant sells these but they can be found all over the place after being sold to merchants.<BR>

I can buy them for ~7pp each but that is crazy. Personally, I think concentration on store-bought poison ingredients is the best idea. But it is totally up to you. I usually bum these off of folks when I pop by SolB. I have been thinking of taking the practice up of buying them from merchants that ppl sold them to just because its more practical now.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>COST IS CORRECT</span><b>, By Roren</b> <small>(3/25/2001)</small><br><br>If you were to make your own vial (which most rogues do) and to collect your own ingreds (which most rogues do) it would only cost the price of the suspension.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>VENDOR SELLS DEATH CAP</span><b>, By Corrik lardbottom, on rallos zek</b> <small>(2/27/2001)</small><br><br>I've noticed that the Death Cap can be bought from the female halfling vendor near the Fool's Gold in Rivervale. Methinks I remember the price being around 8pp, but I'm not absolutely sure. For that price, I'd rather hunt kobolds and cross me fingers for the drop.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>POISON COST</span><b>, By Binluin</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I don't think you have the costs of the poison's right.  You say it's &#34;cost of poison:2pp 1gp 1cp&#34;, but the Larent Suspension, costs &#34;2pp 1gp 1cp&#34;, and the Sealed Vial costs &#34;6pp 3gp 3cp&#34;.  Plus if you had to buy any of the Ingredients.  We are looking at &#34;8pp 4gp 4cp&#34; before the cost of Ingredients.

  <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
